{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/sentiment-analysis-for-apples-csr-report-92e94b18b1ef", "time": 1683004115.271845, "path": "towardsdatascience.com/sentiment-analysis-for-apples-csr-report-92e94b18b1ef/", "webpage": {"metadata": {"title": "Sentiment Analysis for Apple\u2019s CSR Report | by Jason | Towards Data Science", "h1": "Sentiment Analysis for Apple\u2019s CSR Report", "description": "There are millions of reports, articles, websites, books, etc., that can be broken down using sentiment analysis in R. The process allows users to get a faster understanding of the main subject of\u2026"}, "outgoing_paragraph_urls": [{"url": "https://towardsdatascience.com/text-analytics-in-r-ae23df8ee928", "anchor_text": "Text Analytics in R", "paragraph_index": 2}, {"url": "https://www.apple.com/environment/pdf/Apple_Environmental_Responsibility_Report_2019.pdf", "anchor_text": "2019 Corporate Social Responsibility", "paragraph_index": 3}, {"url": "https://github.com/jasonmchlee/text-analytics/blob/master/Corporate%20Social%20Responsibility%20Reports/apple.txt", "anchor_text": "apple.txt", "paragraph_index": 5}, {"url": "https://www.tidytextmining.com/sentiment.html", "anchor_text": "AFINN", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://www.tidytextmining.com/sentiment.html", "anchor_text": "", "paragraph_index": 12}, {"url": "https://www.tidytextmining.com/sentiment.html", "anchor_text": "bing", "paragraph_index": 13}, {"url": "https://www.tidytextmining.com/sentiment.html", "anchor_text": "nrc", "paragraph_index": 16}], "all_paragraphs": ["Have you ever wanted to understand the type of language or tone a report is trying to convey?", "There are millions of reports, articles, websites, books, etc., that can be broken down using sentiment analysis in R. The process allows users to get a faster understanding of the main subject of focus without the need to dive too deep into the text.", "To start with this tutorial, you will need to have beginner/intermediate working knowledge in using R Studio. If you don\u2019t visit my other posts to learn more \u2014 Text Analytics in R", "Visit Apple (or any other site) to obtain its 2019 Corporate Social Responsibility (CSR) report. I prefer reading in data in text format.", "Here is what I did to get the file ready to load into R Studio.", "If you are having trouble in this step, please download my apple.txt file.", "If you haven\u2019t set your working directory to the same location as your Apple.txt file, then you will need to paste in the entire path. Below is the code if you have set your working directory.", "There are three steps we need to take to get our dataframe ready.", "Now we have the text ready to analyze we can use any of the 3 R libraries. We will use the get_sentiments function to obtain insights.", "To use the sentiment function, we will need to tokenize the words and filter out stop_words simultaneously.", "Tokenization is the process of separating each word, making each word an independent point used for analysis. For example, using tokenization, the sentence \u201cThe brown fox jumped,\u201d would be \u201cthe,\u201d \u201cbrown,\u201d \u201cfox,\u201d and \u201cjumped.\u201d", "Stop words will filter out any unnecessary words in the report, for example, \u201cI,\u201d \u201cam,\u201d \u201cthe,\u201d etc.", "The AFINN lexicon assigns words with a score that runs between -5 and 5, with negative scores indicating negative sentiment and positive ratings indicating positive sentiment.", "The binglexicon categorizes words in a binary fashion into positive and negative categories. Following the same structure, we can get the sentiment for the bing library.", "Notice how two things changed in our code. The first one is the \u201cbing\u201d library is loaded instead. The other change was the word sentiment instead of value (Afinn code). This is because the two libraries label their sentiment in different ways.", "We can see the Bing and Afinn results are almost identical.", "And now, my favorite library \u2014 NRC. The nrc lexicon categorizes words in a binary fashion (\u201cyes\u201d/\u201cno\u201d) into categories of positive, negative, anger, anticipation, disgust, fear, joy, sadness, surprise, and trust.", "Again we can see a similar structure as the previous libraries.", "Interesting to see how R separates the same words into different sentiment categories. We have the word resources classified as joy, positive, and trust.", "Now that we have the basic idea of getting sentiment values from our report, we can now prepare for more advanced techniques using text analytics. I will be posting a follow-up tutorial that will dive into wordcloud analysis in R.", "If you want more practice with text analytics in R to check out my other posts.", "Your home for data science. A Medium publication sharing concepts, ideas and codes."], "all_outgoing_urls": [{"url": "https://rsci.app.link/?%24canonical_url=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fp%2F92e94b18b1ef&%7Efeature=LoOpenInAppButton&%7Echannel=ShowPostUnderCollection&source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": "Open in app"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsentiment-analysis-for-apples-csr-report-92e94b18b1ef&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign up"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=login&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Ftowardsdatascience.com%2Fsentiment-analysis-for-apples-csr-report-92e94b18b1ef&source=post_page---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------global_nav-----------", "anchor_text": "Sign In"}, {"url": "https://medium.com/?source=---two_column_layout_nav----------------------------------", "anchor_text": ""}, {"url": "https://medium.com/m/signin?operation=register&redirect=https%3A%2F%2Fmedium.com%2Fnew-story&source=---two_column_layout_nav-----------------------new_post_sidenav-----------", "anchor_text": "